WEBVTT

01:40.460 --> 01:45.940
[Speed and Love]

01:46.330 --> 01:48.729
[Episode 14]

02:02.570 --> 02:03.290
Enough.

02:05.320 --> 02:07.120
I have someone I want to protect.

02:07.480 --> 02:09.410
Stop coming here and acting crazy.

02:30.320 --> 02:31.290
Morning.

02:34.250 --> 02:35.200
Lightning?

02:44.850 --> 02:45.520
Morning.

02:50.760 --> 02:52.730
What is she doing? She's so jumpy.

02:52.780 --> 02:54.240
What's wrong with Sister?

02:55.010 --> 02:56.540
Still half asleep, I guess.

02:57.850 --> 02:59.579
Why are you here so early today?

03:14.290 --> 03:16.290
Zhao said you don't like dumplings,

03:16.450 --> 03:18.060
so I specially made some dishes for you.

03:18.060 --> 03:19.320
You can have some rice.

03:21.570 --> 03:22.360
Thanks.

03:24.130 --> 03:25.060
Here. Thank you.

03:26.400 --> 03:27.030
Thanks.

03:31.560 --> 03:32.320
Is it good?

04:12.480 --> 04:14.080
You don't want to get better?

04:14.450 --> 04:16.250
I want to see if it makes me cough.

04:19.690 --> 04:20.320
No way.

04:20.640 --> 04:22.970
Don't all those women who race cars smoke?

04:23.690 --> 04:24.820
Wan Qing smokes too.

04:25.930 --> 04:27.530
You're different from them.

04:31.050 --> 04:32.110
How am I different?

04:38.570 --> 04:39.970
This answer...

04:40.650 --> 04:42.909
I'm not particularly satisfied with it.

04:43.520 --> 04:44.450
It sounds like

04:44.790 --> 04:46.620
I'm not so special after all.

04:50.870 --> 04:52.870
Then what kind of answer do you want?

04:54.080 --> 04:55.159
For example...

04:57.390 --> 04:58.310
Am I pretty?

05:03.760 --> 05:05.810
Come on, answer my question.

05:06.940 --> 05:07.540
I won't.

05:07.890 --> 05:09.450
No, you have to.

05:09.890 --> 05:10.690
Otherwise,

05:11.080 --> 05:12.840
you'll lose me as your sister.

05:18.560 --> 05:19.400
Then let it be.

05:21.720 --> 05:23.720
No, you must keep me.

05:24.930 --> 05:25.760
Hurry up and answer my question.

05:25.760 --> 05:26.610
Hurry up.

05:26.720 --> 05:27.250
Hurry...

05:35.130 --> 05:35.960
What exactly

05:37.490 --> 05:38.950
kind of answer do you want?

05:44.760 --> 05:46.090
I'll go downstairs now.

05:57.960 --> 06:01.720
[Speeding Auto House]

05:58.200 --> 05:59.260
Package delivery.

06:00.610 --> 06:01.320
Coming!

06:03.240 --> 06:04.100
Be right there!

06:05.320 --> 06:06.980
Hello. A package for Jin Zhao.

06:07.200 --> 06:09.260
It needs the recipient's signature.

06:10.010 --> 06:10.760
Brandy!

06:11.160 --> 06:12.840
There's a package for you
that needs your signature.

06:12.840 --> 06:13.930
It's all letters.

06:13.930 --> 06:14.760
I don't understand.

06:14.760 --> 06:16.360
Maybe you should take a look.

06:33.960 --> 06:34.610
Reject it.

06:35.159 --> 06:35.960
Send it back.

06:36.159 --> 06:36.760
Okay.

06:39.370 --> 06:40.720
You don't accept these imported parts

06:40.720 --> 06:42.090
and only use your handmade ones instead?

06:42.090 --> 06:43.620
Do you think that will work?

06:45.490 --> 06:47.150
Let's just install it and see.

06:47.290 --> 06:48.050
You...

08:40.130 --> 08:40.799
Taste it.

08:43.159 --> 08:44.159
Taste it?

08:44.560 --> 08:45.680
I can tell just by looking.

08:45.680 --> 08:46.610
No progress.

08:48.680 --> 08:49.340
Drink this.

09:22.640 --> 09:23.970
Tell me what's going on.

09:25.800 --> 09:26.850
Your RX7

09:28.400 --> 09:30.160
can hit 700 HP on the dyno.

09:30.800 --> 09:32.130
But when I test-drove it earlier,

09:32.130 --> 09:33.460
before I could floor it,

09:34.250 --> 09:35.910
the engine started knocking.

09:35.930 --> 09:38.530
With a Wankel engine,
knocking is inevitable.

09:41.280 --> 09:42.810
Where did you get the parts?

09:43.520 --> 09:45.120
I didn't use imported parts.

09:45.160 --> 09:46.330
I made some myself.

09:46.610 --> 09:47.610
But when the engine temperature
got too high,

09:47.610 --> 09:49.610
the rotors and the crank started melting

09:49.610 --> 09:50.740
and fused together.

09:51.090 --> 09:52.750
Then buy some imported parts.

09:53.130 --> 09:54.280
You can afford it.

09:56.440 --> 09:58.800
Wan Shengbang
has monopolized all the supplies.

09:58.800 --> 10:00.370
I even tried a bigger radiator,

10:00.370 --> 10:01.400
but it couldn't handle it.

10:01.400 --> 10:02.760
Crank, rotors—

10:03.210 --> 10:05.040
these are all metal.

10:05.040 --> 10:06.440
It's a matter of science,

10:06.440 --> 10:08.700
not something you can solve by yourself.

10:10.440 --> 10:11.770
So there's no other way?

10:11.970 --> 10:13.430
I can only use those parts?

10:15.460 --> 10:17.060
There's always a way.

10:19.760 --> 10:21.890
Since you thought about the radiator,

10:22.330 --> 10:24.390
you should know it's a cooling issue.

10:25.560 --> 10:27.820
But a bigger radiator doesn't help much,

10:28.130 --> 10:29.800
because the engine bay's cooling space

10:29.800 --> 10:30.890
is limited.

10:35.640 --> 10:36.400
Here.

10:37.760 --> 10:38.760
This is...

10:39.520 --> 10:40.680
the intercooler,

10:42.090 --> 10:43.250
the radiator,

10:45.190 --> 10:46.250
and the condenser.

10:46.490 --> 10:47.090
Look.

10:47.250 --> 10:49.520
There's no room left to adjust anything.

10:50.000 --> 10:52.200
So we'll tackle each problem one by one.

10:53.330 --> 10:54.790
The AC is already removed.

10:54.970 --> 10:56.040
Use the extra power

10:56.520 --> 10:58.210
for the cooling fan.

10:59.610 --> 11:00.850
What did I just say?

11:02.130 --> 11:04.250
There's no space left in the engine bay.

11:04.250 --> 11:06.180
But don't you still have the trunk?

11:07.130 --> 11:08.730
Find a spot, add a water tank,

11:08.760 --> 11:10.690
and run a few pipes for water spray.

11:17.280 --> 11:19.920
It can increase cooling capacity
even more.

11:21.400 --> 11:22.860
If there's no space there,

11:23.250 --> 11:24.520
find one elsewhere.

11:26.520 --> 11:29.520
It's still the same logic
of cooling with water spray?

11:30.210 --> 11:32.090
Modifying cars requires brains.

11:33.210 --> 11:34.940
Why compete on metal hardware?

11:35.760 --> 11:37.130
That old fool Wan Shengbang

11:37.130 --> 11:38.790
hasn't learned anything
after all these years.

11:38.790 --> 11:39.880
Same shady tricks

11:39.900 --> 11:41.210
over and over.

11:44.970 --> 11:46.170
You're the smart one.

11:46.890 --> 11:48.040
All these years of drinking

11:48.040 --> 11:49.770
still haven't made you stupid.

11:50.760 --> 11:51.610
You little punk,

11:51.610 --> 11:53.810
you don't want to learn from me anymore?

11:54.490 --> 11:55.220
I'm leaving.

11:55.520 --> 11:56.210
Wait.

11:57.440 --> 11:58.370
What's the rush?

11:58.490 --> 11:59.400
Going to modify the car.

11:59.400 --> 12:00.250
No hurry.

12:02.400 --> 12:03.730
I've got a delivery order here.

12:03.730 --> 12:05.390
Help me deliver it on your way.

12:05.490 --> 12:06.490
Where's the food?

12:07.400 --> 12:08.520
What's the rush?

12:09.760 --> 12:11.090
I haven't cooked it yet.

12:20.640 --> 12:21.370
That much?

12:21.570 --> 12:23.180
A big customer. Go on.

12:24.610 --> 12:26.670
Don't forget to ask for a good review.

12:41.040 --> 12:42.210
Where are you going?

12:43.920 --> 12:45.730
It's okay. Let him in.

13:01.560 --> 13:02.250
Your food.

13:03.330 --> 13:05.860
I heard that restaurant's chef

13:05.890 --> 13:07.760
cooks pretty randomly.

13:09.000 --> 13:10.810
I thought I'd try my luck.

13:15.130 --> 13:16.210
I didn't expect

13:17.520 --> 13:19.650
a surprise delivered right to my door.

13:19.890 --> 13:20.730
Well...

13:22.250 --> 13:23.040
Your parts—

13:24.250 --> 13:25.280
I sent them back.

13:26.520 --> 13:27.680
I appreciate your kindness.

13:27.680 --> 13:29.340
But I don't need them anymore.

13:30.110 --> 13:31.110
This meal is on me.

13:33.850 --> 13:34.490
By the way,

13:36.130 --> 13:37.040
if you're not busy,

13:37.040 --> 13:38.840
remember to leave a good review.

13:39.560 --> 13:40.210
Thanks.

13:41.520 --> 13:42.650
What should I write?

13:42.970 --> 13:44.030
Whatever you want.

13:59.070 --> 14:01.670
The food is really delicious and spicy.

14:01.920 --> 14:04.160
The delivery man is damn hot.

14:15.280 --> 14:16.010
Delete that.

14:16.490 --> 14:18.920
Didn't you ask me
to give you a good review?

14:19.250 --> 14:20.010
I asked you to review the food,

14:20.010 --> 14:21.210
not me.

14:21.440 --> 14:23.240
I asked what to write and you said

14:23.250 --> 14:24.450
"whatever you want."

14:25.920 --> 14:27.850
What will it take for you to delete it?

14:27.850 --> 14:30.490
My fried rice.

14:30.640 --> 14:31.610
I'll make it for you.

14:31.610 --> 14:32.250
When?

14:32.560 --> 14:33.490
Delete it first.

14:33.640 --> 14:34.770
Make it for me first.

14:37.460 --> 14:38.390
Tomorrow night.

14:38.610 --> 14:39.730
At the Chinese restaurant.

14:39.730 --> 14:40.730
Just the two of us?

14:40.970 --> 14:42.280
Of course. Who else will there be?

14:42.280 --> 14:42.920
Okay.

14:43.440 --> 14:44.280
See you there.

14:50.330 --> 14:51.760
Is he really that hot?

14:52.090 --> 14:54.220
Pics or it didn't happen. Post a photo.

14:54.440 --> 14:55.890
I'll arrive in Manshi tomorrow.

14:55.890 --> 14:57.040
I'm going out for dinner in the evening.

14:57.040 --> 14:58.370
Will I be able to see him?

14:58.890 --> 14:59.890
Tomorrow?

15:00.330 --> 15:01.210
Sorry,

15:01.370 --> 15:02.700
you won't get to see him.

15:22.680 --> 15:24.280
I haven't seen him for 2 days.

15:24.920 --> 15:26.320
What's he been busy with?

15:26.920 --> 15:29.210
Sanlai said he went to Qingshi.

15:30.010 --> 15:31.280
Qingshi again?

15:32.160 --> 15:33.250
I wonder if he's

15:33.400 --> 15:35.330
doing something dangerous again.

15:37.390 --> 15:40.620
[Zhao]

15:48.330 --> 15:49.560
I must trust Zhao.

15:50.130 --> 15:52.130
He'll definitely come back safely.

16:11.770 --> 16:14.430
Currently,
Liang Yanfeng's 350Z is in the lead.

16:15.250 --> 16:16.730
He gained an advantage in the first half

16:16.730 --> 16:18.190
and is currently in front.

16:27.210 --> 16:27.920
D-God,

16:28.370 --> 16:30.230
who do you think will take second?

16:30.910 --> 16:32.240
I only care about first,

16:32.560 --> 16:33.640
not second.

18:07.850 --> 18:10.180
DRZ wants to overtake but lacks the skill.

18:10.640 --> 18:11.530
Now it comes down to

18:11.530 --> 18:13.190
Jin Zhao's RX7 versus the S200

18:13.210 --> 18:14.340
to see who's better.

18:27.270 --> 18:29.310
Brandy, 600 HP is your limit.

18:29.810 --> 18:32.010
It would be embarrassing if you blow it.

18:32.260 --> 18:33.460
Thanks for your concern.

18:33.460 --> 18:34.520
That's your limit,

18:34.590 --> 18:35.400
not mine.

18:41.400 --> 18:43.590
RX7 is accelerating
and trying to overtake,

18:43.590 --> 18:45.160
but Feng's defense is tight.

18:45.160 --> 18:45.920
Passing

18:46.290 --> 18:47.400
won't be easy.

19:26.110 --> 19:27.310
RX7 disappeared!

19:30.610 --> 19:31.810
No, it didn't.

19:32.130 --> 19:33.660
It's still on the main line.

19:33.720 --> 19:35.290
He seems to have turned off
the headlights.

19:35.290 --> 19:36.550
What is he trying to do?

20:09.000 --> 20:10.800
Jin Zhao's RX7 is in first place.

20:12.720 --> 20:14.250
RX7 is still accelerating!

20:14.770 --> 20:15.530
600 HP!

20:16.440 --> 20:17.440
650 HP!

20:18.680 --> 20:20.850
It looks like RX7 has gone past 700 HP.

20:21.200 --> 20:23.810
D-God,
why did RX7 turn off its headlights?

20:25.090 --> 20:26.720
It reduces wind resistance,

20:26.890 --> 20:28.850
helps with a full-throttle sprint,

20:28.850 --> 20:30.510
and throws off the opponents.

20:30.570 --> 20:32.570
Most people wouldn't dare drive like that.

20:32.570 --> 20:33.930
Even without imported parts,

20:33.930 --> 20:35.370
he still managed to push the Wankel engine

20:35.370 --> 20:36.640
to its limit

20:36.920 --> 20:38.680
without overheating.

20:38.800 --> 20:39.840
Interesting.

20:45.510 --> 20:46.920
Brandy, you're going hard tonight.

20:46.920 --> 20:49.850
You've already qualified.
No need to risk your life.

21:03.000 --> 21:05.480
The Wankel-powered RX7
crossed the finish line!

21:05.480 --> 21:08.200
Tonight's champion is RX7!

21:18.530 --> 21:19.400
Not bad.

21:20.330 --> 21:21.460
You did it again.

21:45.050 --> 21:46.510
You went back on your word.

21:47.160 --> 21:48.370
We agreed on tonight.

21:53.810 --> 21:54.570
I'm sorry.

21:55.570 --> 21:57.430
I forgot there was a race tonight.

21:57.830 --> 21:59.960
Let me find a place for us to celebrate.

22:05.870 --> 22:07.220
[Professional Oversleeper: Where are you?]

22:09.440 --> 22:10.100
No, thanks.

22:11.810 --> 22:12.850
Maybe another day.

22:12.850 --> 22:14.160
You look tired.

22:14.290 --> 22:15.570
Find a place to rest.

22:16.440 --> 22:17.970
I need to get back to Manshi.

22:18.720 --> 22:19.720
Overnight?

22:21.290 --> 22:21.960
By the way,

22:23.100 --> 22:25.230
how did you manage the cooling system?

22:25.530 --> 22:26.930
Radiator, intercooler,

22:27.200 --> 22:28.370
and AC evaporator—

22:28.640 --> 22:29.850
arranged at certain angles.

22:29.850 --> 22:31.130
Who taught you that?

22:31.960 --> 22:33.690
That uncle who's always drunk.

23:01.310 --> 23:02.070
Going out?

23:13.810 --> 23:15.940
I haven't seen you for a few days again.

23:16.200 --> 23:17.610
Still busy lately?

23:20.920 --> 23:22.640
Why are you in such a hurry to save money?

23:22.640 --> 23:23.890
Eager to get married?

23:27.000 --> 23:28.800
Can you introduce someone to me?

23:29.000 --> 23:29.810
Sure.

23:30.150 --> 23:32.550
There are many beautiful girls
in my class.

23:34.370 --> 23:35.130
I'm too busy.

23:35.680 --> 23:37.140
I don't have time for that.

23:50.970 --> 23:52.890
When you messaged me last night,

23:53.680 --> 23:54.940
I was still in Qingshi.

23:55.570 --> 23:57.480
I rushed back overnight
to take you to school.

23:57.480 --> 23:59.480
And you're still pouting like this?

23:59.890 --> 24:01.480
I'm not pouting.

24:04.920 --> 24:05.920
See for yourself.

24:08.090 --> 24:08.770
I'm not.

24:11.680 --> 24:13.210
Let's go. Or you'll be late.

25:11.570 --> 25:12.500
I'm not leaving.

25:13.540 --> 25:14.670
I'll watch you go in.

25:25.290 --> 25:27.020
I'll wait for you after school,

25:27.530 --> 25:29.060
take you back to the garage,

25:29.410 --> 25:31.270
and make something tasty for you.

25:32.330 --> 25:33.190
Give me a smile.

26:02.160 --> 26:03.290
Focus on your class.

26:03.530 --> 26:04.860
I'll be waiting for you.

26:13.090 --> 26:15.220
Why do you suddenly want to cook today?

26:15.520 --> 26:17.690
You guys have always cooked for me before.

26:17.690 --> 26:18.960
Today I want to show you my skills.

26:18.960 --> 26:20.810
And hasn't Sanlai been saying
he wants to eat

26:20.810 --> 26:22.670
squirrel-shaped mandarin fish?

26:28.130 --> 26:29.860
Which one is the mandarin fish?

26:30.570 --> 26:31.240
This one.

26:33.330 --> 26:35.240
Sir, please gut this fish.

26:35.240 --> 26:36.770
You'll have to wait in line.

26:39.400 --> 26:40.530
Then just wrap it up.

26:41.160 --> 26:41.920
Okay.

26:43.130 --> 26:45.240
Don't they help gut the fish here?

26:45.960 --> 26:47.560
Can't you see there's a line?

26:48.980 --> 26:50.580
You know how to gut it, right?

26:51.060 --> 26:52.030
Don't worry.

26:52.130 --> 26:53.370
How can I not worry?

26:53.720 --> 26:54.770
350.

26:58.610 --> 26:59.290
Thank you.

27:03.200 --> 27:04.090
That guy...

27:04.240 --> 27:06.770
That guy has been to the garage before,
right?

27:12.170 --> 27:13.100
I don't know him.

27:13.330 --> 27:14.160
You don't?

27:15.160 --> 27:17.890
I think I've seen him
at the garage before.

27:18.640 --> 27:19.770
Don't you remember?

27:21.440 --> 27:22.900
Do you know how many people

27:23.050 --> 27:24.610
come to the garage every day?

27:24.610 --> 27:25.850
I'm swamped.

27:26.200 --> 27:28.200
How can I remember everyone's face?

27:36.460 --> 27:37.640
Here you go, sir.

27:37.920 --> 27:39.850
-Thank you.
-Thank you for coming.

27:44.890 --> 27:47.020
Is there anything else you want to eat?

27:48.130 --> 27:49.390
This should be enough.

27:49.570 --> 27:50.440
Then wait here for me.

27:50.440 --> 27:51.570
I need to make a call.

28:02.730 --> 28:03.360
What is it?

28:17.920 --> 28:19.240
Check out the fruit.

28:19.640 --> 28:20.770
What would you like?

28:25.940 --> 28:27.070
I'll take two boxes.

28:27.480 --> 28:28.610
100 per box.

28:32.530 --> 28:33.930
If we wait another month,

28:34.160 --> 28:36.160
strawberries will be much cheaper.

28:36.400 --> 28:38.660
What if you don't want them a month later?

28:40.160 --> 28:41.760
Who said I wanted to eat them?

28:43.510 --> 28:44.230
I want them.

28:46.610 --> 28:47.570
Thank you.

28:59.960 --> 29:01.200
Is there enough oil?

29:09.990 --> 29:10.660
Let me.

29:10.770 --> 29:12.160
No need. I can handle it.

29:34.280 --> 29:36.460
♪ What would I do ♪

29:36.160 --> 29:37.610
Didn't you say you wanted strawberries?

29:36.490 --> 29:38.960
♪ If I have 45 minutes? ♪

29:38.260 --> 29:39.220
Was it me?

29:39.510 --> 29:42.220
♪ Would I write a song? ♪

29:39.850 --> 29:40.980
You said it earlier.

29:42.700 --> 29:44.850
♪ I don't think so ♪

29:46.420 --> 29:48.690
♪ What would I do ♪

29:48.240 --> 29:49.240
I'll help.

29:48.740 --> 29:51.100
♪ If I have 70 seconds? ♪

29:51.370 --> 29:54.100
♪ Would I get a drink or two? ♪

29:54.650 --> 29:57.110
♪ No, I don't think so ♪

29:57.930 --> 30:01.120
♪ I'd rather get on that bus ♪

30:01.650 --> 30:04.340
♪ Find you where you are ♪

30:04.810 --> 30:07.060
♪ To talk about the cloud ♪

30:07.250 --> 30:09.910
♪ That looks just like a kangaroo ♪

30:10.690 --> 30:13.660
♪ And the old man on the street ♪

30:14.000 --> 30:16.830
♪ Sat there with his dog ♪

30:17.240 --> 30:19.540
♪ Asking you if you're willing ♪

30:18.000 --> 30:18.680
Sugar.

30:19.570 --> 30:22.040
♪ To accompany me too ♪

30:28.550 --> 30:30.790
♪ Would you like that? ♪

30:31.460 --> 30:34.360
♪ Would you like that? ♪

30:34.920 --> 30:35.960
All done!

30:40.640 --> 30:41.700
Smells delicious.

30:48.110 --> 30:50.430
♪ What would I do? ♪

30:50.460 --> 30:53.200
♪ If I could fly up on the roof ♪

30:53.920 --> 30:55.810
♪ Would I rob a bank? ♪

30:56.250 --> 30:58.950
♪ Oh, I don't think so ♪

31:00.310 --> 31:02.630
♪ What would I do? ♪

31:02.660 --> 31:05.890
♪ If I could turn invisible ♪

31:05.910 --> 31:08.390
♪ Would I drive my favorite car? ♪

31:08.470 --> 31:11.210
♪ No, I don't think so ♪

31:11.000 --> 31:11.810
Here.

31:12.000 --> 31:15.200
♪ I'd go to the restaurant ♪

31:15.700 --> 31:18.270
♪ Steal all the fortune cookies ♪

31:17.130 --> 31:18.400
This is so delicious!

31:18.850 --> 31:21.270
♪ Read them one by one ♪

31:19.050 --> 31:21.110
Mu, did you make all this by yourself?

31:21.290 --> 31:22.480
♪ Till it says ♪

31:22.510 --> 31:24.360
♪ That I could be with you ♪

31:24.720 --> 31:27.270
♪ Sneak into the flower shop ♪

31:25.920 --> 31:26.480
Yes.

31:26.850 --> 31:27.710
All by herself.

31:27.760 --> 31:30.770
♪ Watch how they make their bouquets ♪

31:28.610 --> 31:29.680
It tastes exactly

31:30.050 --> 31:30.890
like that takeout

31:30.890 --> 31:31.680
I had last time.

31:30.930 --> 31:34.340
♪ So I could finally used ♪

31:31.890 --> 31:32.890
This is really delicious.

31:32.890 --> 31:34.640
Really? Let me try some.

31:34.480 --> 31:36.960
♪ The flowers I planted just for you ♪

31:34.960 --> 31:36.050
Perfect, Sanlai.

31:36.050 --> 31:38.610
this squirrel-shaped mandarin fish
was made especially for you.

31:38.610 --> 31:40.050
Especially for me?

31:40.640 --> 31:42.400
You put in a lot of effort. Thank you.

31:42.400 --> 31:44.490
♪ Would you like that? ♪

31:44.450 --> 31:45.690
How did you make the sauce?

31:45.360 --> 31:47.490
♪ Would you like that? ♪

31:45.720 --> 31:46.770
Why is it so thick?

31:47.330 --> 31:49.200
I just used ketchup,

31:49.480 --> 31:51.140
stir-fried it a bit in the pan,

31:51.400 --> 31:54.530
then added a little white wine,
cooking wine, and sugar.

31:54.650 --> 31:56.810
♪ Would you like that? ♪

31:54.740 --> 31:55.540
What's wrong?

31:56.050 --> 31:56.720
Nothing.

31:57.720 --> 31:59.090
So complicated?

31:57.730 --> 31:59.810
♪ Would you like that? ♪

31:59.240 --> 32:00.240
I thought it would be super easy.

32:00.240 --> 32:01.260
I thought you only needed

32:01.260 --> 32:02.400
-to pour the sauce over it.
-Really.

32:02.400 --> 32:04.010
There are tutorials online.

32:07.050 --> 32:09.670
♪ Would you like that? ♪

32:10.150 --> 32:12.930
♪ Would you like that? ♪

32:40.850 --> 32:41.780
Have some juice.

32:47.160 --> 32:47.850
Zhao,

32:48.640 --> 32:49.500
have you been in

32:49.680 --> 32:51.530
some kind of trouble lately?

32:51.920 --> 32:52.960
You can tell me.

32:53.190 --> 32:55.000
Maybe I can help.

32:58.720 --> 32:59.520
It's nothing.

33:07.850 --> 33:10.510
It smells so good.
I want some strong coffee too.

33:11.130 --> 33:12.130
You're too young.

33:12.240 --> 33:13.640
No strong coffee for you.

33:25.380 --> 33:26.230
Brandy,

33:27.050 --> 33:28.130
I heard about it.

33:28.680 --> 33:30.140
Top three in the alliance.

33:30.170 --> 33:31.000
Impressive.

33:32.290 --> 33:33.680
So, tomorrow,

33:34.090 --> 33:35.090
let's celebrate.

33:35.160 --> 33:36.610
Let's invite a few friends.

33:36.610 --> 33:37.890
Bring Jiang Mu too.

33:38.370 --> 33:38.900
Okay.

33:45.160 --> 33:45.920
Is it good?

33:49.030 --> 33:51.180
I guess I really am too young.

34:25.850 --> 34:28.310
This courtyard
has such a great atmosphere.

34:29.000 --> 34:30.260
You mean these lights?

34:30.480 --> 34:31.480
They're the only thing

34:31.480 --> 34:32.850
my ex left me.

34:33.040 --> 34:33.969
Where is she now?

34:34.120 --> 34:35.290
She's my ex now.

34:35.650 --> 34:36.889
She once had a fight with me

34:36.889 --> 34:38.100
over something trivial

34:38.100 --> 34:39.560
and threatened to break up.

34:39.560 --> 34:40.820
I didn't give in to her.

34:40.960 --> 34:42.020
Then she got angry,

34:42.250 --> 34:43.850
packed her things, and left.

34:43.900 --> 34:44.830
Never came back.

34:45.440 --> 34:47.400
Crazy Jin isn't good with women.

34:47.780 --> 34:49.120
He goes through many breakups every year.

34:49.120 --> 34:50.620
None of his relationships
lasted over 3 months.

34:50.620 --> 34:52.409
What are you talking about?

34:53.480 --> 34:55.480
Nana and I lasted more than 6 months.

34:56.080 --> 34:57.820
You have the nerve to say that?

34:58.330 --> 34:59.440
You dated for 2 months,

34:59.440 --> 35:01.480
broke up for 6 months,
then got back together for half a month.

35:01.480 --> 35:02.330
That's two and a half months total.

35:02.330 --> 35:03.440
Not even 3.

35:04.080 --> 35:05.520
How are you counting?

35:06.370 --> 35:09.370
The whole process lasted 6 months.
That's half a year.

35:09.370 --> 35:11.100
You two aren't much different.

35:11.120 --> 35:12.810
But your ex was also called Nana?

35:12.810 --> 35:14.290
All his exes

35:14.400 --> 35:16.370
were either Nana or Nini.

35:16.520 --> 35:18.180
Same names, different girls.

35:19.400 --> 35:20.890
You have the nerve to say that?

35:20.890 --> 35:22.440
You're still single.

35:24.730 --> 35:25.600
Sanlai.

35:26.330 --> 35:27.890
You've never had a girlfriend?

35:27.890 --> 35:28.690
No.

35:29.040 --> 35:31.330
He's been single since birth.

35:32.700 --> 35:34.700
Didn't you date Nana before?

35:35.520 --> 35:37.800
What are you saying? Don't talk nonsense.

35:37.800 --> 35:39.930
We were just neighbors for a few years.

35:42.080 --> 35:44.330
His dad was my aunt's ex-boyfriend.

35:44.690 --> 35:45.650
Your aunt?

35:46.690 --> 35:47.770
Lin Sui's mother?

35:47.850 --> 35:49.600
No, not Lin Sui's. Another aunt.

35:49.600 --> 35:51.210
Sanlai's mom is from Northeast China.

35:51.210 --> 35:52.290
She was my mom's college classmate.

35:52.290 --> 35:54.170
So we've known each other since childhood.

35:54.170 --> 35:55.770
After his parents divorced,

35:55.900 --> 35:56.960
his dad took him and moved away,

35:56.960 --> 35:58.820
so we weren't neighbors anymore.

35:58.890 --> 36:00.080
Northeast China?

36:00.600 --> 36:02.330
No wonder Sanlai's eating habits

36:02.330 --> 36:03.260
are so northern.

36:03.290 --> 36:05.000
He loves noodles and dumplings.

36:05.000 --> 36:06.250
He doesn't just eat them himself.

36:06.250 --> 36:07.330
He makes us eat too.

36:07.440 --> 36:09.120
Now our eating habits

36:09.520 --> 36:10.980
are all influenced by him.

36:16.170 --> 36:18.210
Why did it take you so long
to bring the alcohol?

36:18.210 --> 36:20.340
Come on, why did you only bring one box?

36:20.400 --> 36:22.060
This isn't enough for anyone.

36:22.210 --> 36:23.870
Can you even handle that much?

36:24.000 --> 36:26.130
My nickname is "Box-by-box Drinker."

36:26.700 --> 36:27.300
Come on.

36:27.810 --> 36:29.080
Mu, one for you.

36:31.890 --> 36:32.490
Yang.

36:33.360 --> 36:34.860
-Don't drink too much.
-Here.

36:34.860 --> 36:35.860
Thank you, Crazy.

36:38.230 --> 36:39.390
We're at my place today.

36:39.390 --> 36:41.520
There are plenty of drinks.
Help yourselves.

36:41.520 --> 36:43.400
I'll be upset
if someone doesn't drink enough.

36:43.400 --> 36:43.850
Come on!

36:43.850 --> 36:44.920
-Let's drink together.
-Here, here.

36:44.920 --> 36:45.730
Bottoms up!

36:47.930 --> 36:48.370
Catch the ducks!

36:48.370 --> 36:49.000
How many?

36:49.370 --> 36:49.910
Quack!

36:50.600 --> 36:52.000
-I said "how many!"
-You have to catch them first.

36:52.000 --> 36:52.600
You haven't caught them yet.

36:52.600 --> 36:53.400
I can't keep up.

36:53.400 --> 36:55.800
-I'll punish myself with a drink.
-Come on.

36:56.960 --> 36:57.950
Cheers.

36:58.910 --> 36:59.970
-Come on.
-Come on.

37:00.900 --> 37:01.850
It's such a fun day.

37:01.850 --> 37:03.310
Why didn't Iron Cock come?

37:04.120 --> 37:05.850
He had to go home for something.

37:06.690 --> 37:08.270
Alright, let's continue.

37:08.400 --> 37:10.210
Let's continue. Starting with you.

37:10.210 --> 37:11.140
Catch the ducks!

37:11.160 --> 37:11.930
How many?

37:11.960 --> 37:12.730
Five!

37:12.810 --> 37:13.520
Got them!

37:13.850 --> 37:14.250
Quack.

37:14.640 --> 37:15.100
Quack.

37:15.120 --> 37:15.600
Quack.

38:01.340 --> 38:01.770
Catch the ducks!

38:01.770 --> 38:02.210
How many?

38:02.210 --> 38:02.810
Three!

38:03.170 --> 38:03.700
Got them!

38:03.760 --> 38:04.510
-Quack.
-Quack.

38:04.510 --> 38:04.850
Quack.

38:04.850 --> 38:05.400
Catch the ducks!

38:05.400 --> 38:06.000
How many?

38:11.630 --> 38:12.760
I need to take a call.

38:12.820 --> 38:13.810
Hey, get me some more skewers.

38:13.810 --> 38:14.490
Get me some skewers.

38:14.490 --> 38:16.210
-Crazy Jin wants skewers.
-This is good.

38:16.210 --> 38:17.520
The balcony is good, right?

38:17.520 --> 38:17.960
It's awesome.

38:17.960 --> 38:20.290
Come by more often. Make yourself at home.

38:20.440 --> 38:21.100
No problem.

38:21.210 --> 38:21.690
Okay.

38:21.770 --> 38:22.960
Let's switch to another game.

38:22.960 --> 38:24.770
Let's play this. Let's play cards.

38:24.770 --> 38:26.040
Let me think...

38:26.440 --> 38:29.100
Just guess black or red
and compare the numbers.

38:29.250 --> 38:30.310
Starting with you.

38:31.080 --> 38:31.850
Black or red?

38:31.960 --> 38:32.560
Black.

38:32.780 --> 38:33.410
Red.

38:34.290 --> 38:35.060
See?

38:35.250 --> 38:36.580
-It's black.
-Drink up!

38:36.600 --> 38:38.130
The first one, black or red?

38:38.400 --> 38:38.960
Black.

38:39.560 --> 38:40.120
Drink up.

38:40.850 --> 38:41.440
Red.

38:41.940 --> 38:43.470
-Drink up.
-I'll drink too.

38:43.730 --> 38:44.210
You.

38:44.290 --> 38:44.850
Black.

38:45.770 --> 38:47.370
You don't need to do it. Skip.

39:05.330 --> 39:05.880
Okay.

39:06.920 --> 39:08.180
I'll talk to you when I get home.

39:08.180 --> 39:09.240
I'm hanging up now.

39:31.080 --> 39:31.890
Are you drunk?

39:32.480 --> 39:33.170
No.

39:33.850 --> 39:35.080
I'm perfectly sober.
